WEBVTT

00:02.955 --> 00:06.305
Tickets this way
for the Chatsworth Express.

00:06.515 --> 00:10.242
Come and watch pikeys
making a mess of the lives

00:10.682 --> 00:14.445
they were given by 'im upstairs.

00:14.485 --> 00:17.852
And kids they're convinced
aren't actually theirs.

00:17.892 --> 00:19.106
Stay away!

00:19.146 --> 00:20.174
What sounds on earth

00:20.214 --> 00:22.076
could ever replace

00:22.116 --> 00:25.687
kids needing money
or wives in your face.

00:25.727 --> 00:28.295
Cos this, people reckon,
and me included,

00:28.335 --> 00:33.217
is why pubs and drugs
were kindly invented -

00:33.257 --> 00:36.923
to calm us all down
to stop us going mental.

00:36.963 --> 00:41.330
These are Chatsworth Estate's
basic essentials.

00:41.370 --> 00:43.549
We are worth every penny

00:43.589 --> 00:45.723
for grinding your axes.

00:45.763 --> 00:48.124
You shit on our heads...

00:48.164 --> 00:50.285
but you pay the taxes.

00:53.377 --> 00:56.407
Imagine a Britain
without Chatsworth buccaneers,

00:56.447 --> 00:58.801
who'd come on your face
for the price of a beer.

00:58.841 --> 01:02.682
Make poverty history,
cheaper drugs now!

01:02.722 --> 01:06.834
Make poverty history,
cheaper drugs now!

01:09.117 --> 01:11.756
Scatter. Party!

01:11.757 --> 01:18.157
www.addic7ed.com

01:18.592 --> 01:21.892
I once fell in love
with a man I'd never met.

01:21.902 --> 01:24.508
Actor. Movie star.

01:24.518 --> 01:27.006
Handsome thing.

01:27.046 --> 01:31.529
Dangerous lips. The promise of sin
in smouldering brown eyes.

01:31.569 --> 01:33.604
I wanted him.

01:33.644 --> 01:36.641
I wanted him so badly it hurt.

01:39.521 --> 01:43.300
Years later, I was working
in a bookshop and in he walks.

01:43.340 --> 01:45.929
Out of fantasy and into the flesh.

01:45.939 --> 01:48.229
And we talked. Laughed.

01:48.269 --> 01:51.451
But it wasn't too long before I
realised that the man I loved

01:51.461 --> 01:55.231
was capable only of loving himself.

01:55.271 --> 02:01.958
Meeting him ruined every
memory of him I'd ever held dear.

02:01.998 --> 02:05.736
I've never watched
a film of his since.

02:05.776 --> 02:10.616
The fantasy is always better
than the reality.

02:17.830 --> 02:23.100
Eamonn, Eamonn, yes, Eamonn! Oh, God
I'm coming. Oh, God, I'm coming.

02:23.140 --> 02:24.381
I'm coming, aaaah!

02:24.421 --> 02:25.871
Libby!

02:30.622 --> 02:34.514
She made this horrible
moaning noise, kept shouting,

02:34.554 --> 02:39.011
"Eamonn, Eamonn!" Then cried out
to God that she were coming.

02:39.051 --> 02:41.825
Can you imagine
how terrible that must be?

02:41.865 --> 02:43.411
A prisoner in your own body,

02:43.451 --> 02:46.850
your only escape -
your only release - in your dreams.

02:46.890 --> 02:49.879
That's all they are, babe, you know,
just dreams, there's nowt in 'em.

02:49.919 --> 02:52.643
I still dream of boffing Monica.

02:56.834 --> 02:57.985
Your nerves must be shot to pieces.

02:58.025 --> 03:00.956
Agh, he's not the only one
- look at that.

03:00.966 --> 03:03.116
I thought the poor
old love was a goner.

03:07.727 --> 03:09.069
Why don't you get yourself
down the pub?

03:11.765 --> 03:12.714
That's my drinking hand.

03:12.754 --> 03:15.399
That's my drinking hand. Which is
why you're only getting a tenner.

